Spanish Inflation Slowed in June as Economic Slump Persists

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-06-30T07:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/spanish-inflation-slowed-in-june-as-economic-slump-persists.html
Spanish consumer prices rose 3
percent in June from a year earlier, as inflation slowed from
the previous month.  The inflation rate, based on European Union calculations,
slowed from 3.4 percent in May, the National Statistics
Institute said today in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas in Madrid at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  